					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I think this was pointed out already, but any NES or Famicom cannot have any kind of &quot;stereo sound&quot; and never will. The console was designed to be mono. Separating bass and trebles and send each one to each speaker is NOT &quot;true stereo sound&quot;.<br /><br />RGB and S-video can be a nice to have though, even if I don't personally care.</div>

